text:
Keg at the brewery druing RBWG Booze Buseday 20/02/15.
Mahogany brown topped with a decent off white swirl.
Nose is nutty, roasted characteristics, toffee, light cocoa rub, spice.
Taste comprises oaky tones, toffee, light roast, cocoa powder, earthy dark fruit shreds.
Medium bodied, fine carbonation, semi drying close.
Solid enough for the style.
user_location: Hazlemere, the lower Xhitlerns, Buckinghamshire, ENGLAND

text: Keg @ Rapp Brewing during RBWG. Cheers to the Rapp Crew! Deep amber pour with a small white head. Decent sweet/earthy character on the nose. Dark cocoa-rubbed plums. Fruit leather and some tree root. Taste is fairly sweet and substantial. Sweet dark grains. Brown toast and a bit of marmalade. Toasted nut. Somewhat hot. Full body.
2/20/15. On tap at the brewpub. Dark amber pour with a small khaki head. Ligh fruity aroma, banana, prunes, toffee. Good flavor, dark fruits, chocolate, pale malts, toffee, burnt caramel. Not bad.

Enjoyed at the Rapp brewery stop of the rbwg2015 bus tour. Poured up on tap where it exhibits a nice mahogany colored body that supports a thin tan head. The aroma offers up plenty of prune and raisin and a dash of cherry sweet dark fruity esters with some malts in the background. The taste is similar but has far lighter sweet dark fruity esters notes. I get a pleasing dose of chocolate malts, an earthy wet tobacco yumminess leading into biscuit and a bit of caramel malts. Behind the malts lurks modest spicy to almost resiny hop notes.
Draft at Rapp Brewing during the RBWG 2015 bus tour. Dark brown with off-white head. Aromas of roast, light chocolate. Tastes of roast, dark fruit, licorice. Medium-light body with a dry finish.
Draft. Pours dark brown tan head. Nose/taste of coffee, toast black malt, banana and wheat. Medium body.
On tap at the brewery during RBWG. Pours a dark amber with small off white head that lasts. The aroma is dark fruit, raisin, caramel. Medium mouth, rich malt, dark fruit, nice dry finish, very good.
Draft - Light toasty, raisin, and dark malts. Dark cloudy brown with a thin white head. Light toast and some grains with a dry finish.

On tap at the brewery 
Clear dark brown with a small beige head, some lacing. Aroma of toasted malts, nutty and caramel. Flavors of toasted malts and caramel 
Nice
Draft at the source during RBWG 2015. Hazy amber brown color, tan head. Aroma and flavor of burnt cocoa and nutella. Tasty.
Draft. Nose is rich german malt, bread, light chocolate and cocoa powder with some light fruitiness. Taste is similar with a grainy wheat character.

Draft. Minimal beige head atop dark red-brown body. Aroma is moderately sweet, caramel, brown sugar, light orange, spicy, banana. Taste is moderately sweet, caramel, some toffee, orange, light molasses, banana. Medium body, some stickiness, low carbonation.
Draft at source. Delicious. Dark amber. Tall pour. Pleasant sweet aroma. Caramel chocolate- smooth flavor. No bite. No complaints but then it is Friday happy hour.

Draft... Pours hazy and dark brown with a small, creamy, white head. The aroma is a delicate blend of roastiness, chocolate and banana. Full-bodied with busy carbonation. Trends a bit sweet with fruity, starchy banana and a faint, unobtrusive, clove-like phenol. Finishes tangy with banana and minerals.
Poured dark amber with aromas of malt, dark fruit and some and some toffee. Flavors are the same with some light earth in the aftertaste.
Brown pour with off white head. Aroma is light toast malt. Taste is light roast malt. Descent beer. Not mely favorite.
On tap at Rapp. Nose is roasted malts, light toffee, a touch of dark fruits. Thin body, dark brown appearance. Flavor is roast and lightly fruity. Good.
Deep brown... Thin tan lacing... Doct sweet.. Malts. Soft banana toffee malts.. Sweet fruirs... Toffee.. Rich sweet fruits.. Toffee malts
Tap at rapp. Chocolate brown pour. Chocolate toffee light tobacco aroma. Taste is like a brown ale. Good light drinking. I could enjoy this as a six pack out side with friends.
draft at Rapp, dark purple grape colored ale, touches of ruby. Sweet maltiness, cloves, herbal notes, dark fruits, raisins. Decent
on tap-tan-dk copper. A-med malt-caramel, banana. T-med malt-roasty/caramel, banana, some earthy hops.
